---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---
<Layout title="The HeadGenome Project" description="A structural and behavioral taxonomy of attention heads in large language models.">

<!-- ── HERO ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="hero">
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <p class="hero-eyebrow reveal">Mechanistic Interpretability · 2025</p>
    <h1 class="hero-title reveal">The HeadGenome<br/>Project</h1>
    <p class="hero-sub reveal">
      A structural and behavioral taxonomy of attention heads<br/>
      in large language models.
    </p>

    <!-- README-style key findings list -->
    <ol class="findings-list reveal">
      <li>
        <strong>The V/Q Spatial Scaling Law</strong>
        <span>An attention head's functional role is strictly governed by its ‖W_V‖/‖W_Q‖ norm ratio — a mathematically inevitable spatial progression through network depth.</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Circuit Co-Gating</strong>
        <span>Retrieval heads and Induction heads cannot function independently. They form a co-dependent pipeline: 0% recovery ablating either alone, 96.5% ablating both together.</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Architecture-Intrinsic Universality</strong>
        <span>The taxonomy survives shuffled tokens, cross-domain training (English, Code, Math), and untrained-control comparison. It is a geometric property of transformers, not of language.</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>The Perplexity Illusion</strong>
        <span>A model can preserve near-perfect perplexity while its long-range retrieval has completely collapsed. Standard evaluation metrics are blind to this failure mode.</span>
      </li>
    </ol>

    <div class="hero-actions reveal">
      <a href={`${base}/taxonomy`} class="hero-btn-primary">Explore the findings</a>
      <a href={`${base}/explorer`} class="hero-btn-secondary">Browse 1,568 heads</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ── HEADLINE NUMBERS ───────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="numbers-section">
  <div class="stat-grid">
    <div class="stat-card c-blue reveal">
      <div class="stat-num">1,568</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Attention heads classified<br/>across four architectures</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card c-purple reveal">
      <div class="stat-num">96.5%</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Retrieval + Induction<br/>co-ablation recovery</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card c-orange reveal">
      <div class="stat-num">13.3×</div>
      <div class="stat-label">KV-cache compression<br/>measured on Llama-3.2-1B</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card c-red reveal">
      <div class="stat-num">10⁻¹²⁷</div>
      <div class="stat-label">V/Q scaling law<br/>p-value</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ── ATLAS ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="atlas-section">
  <div class="atlas-inner">
    <div class="atlas-text reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow">The HeadGenome Atlas</p>
      <h2>Every head, mapped.</h2>
      <p>
        Projecting all 1,568 heads onto the (V/Q ratio, entropy) plane produces a 2D map
        in which the four functional classes occupy non-overlapping, reproducible regions
        across every model tested — GPT-2 (MHA), Qwen-0.5B, Qwen-1.5B, and Llama-3.2-1B (GQA).
      </p>
      <div class="type-pills">
        <span class="pill pill-sink">Sink</span>
        <span class="pill pill-local">Local</span>
        <span class="pill pill-retrieval">Retrieval</span>
        <span class="pill pill-induction">Induction</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="atlas-fig reveal">
      <canvas id="atlas-canvas" role="img" aria-label="Animated HeadGenome atlas"></canvas>
      <p class="atlas-caption">1,568 heads assembling into their learned positions — animated on load</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ── VISUAL EVIDENCE ────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="evidence-section">
  <div class="evidence-inner">
    <p class="eyebrow reveal">Visual evidence · Figures 1–12</p>
    <p class="evidence-intro reveal">
      Every claim in HeadGenome is backed by a figure. Here is the complete visual story —
      mirroring the structure of the master report.
    </p>

    {[
      {
        n: '1', title: 'The V/Q Spatial Scaling Law',
        src: `${base}/figures/fig1_vq_scaling.png`,
        caption: 'The ‖W_V‖/‖W_Q‖ norm ratio rises monotonically with depth across all four architectures. p ≈ 1.92 × 10⁻¹²⁷.',
      },
      {
        n: '2', title: 'The Bifurcation Axis',
        src: `${base}/figures/fig2_bifurcation.png`,
        caption: 'At 40–60% depth, the developmental manifold splits: most heads remain Local; a minority specialise into Retrieval or Induction.',
      },
      {
        n: '3', title: 'The HeadGenome Atlas',
        src: `${base}/figures/atlas.png`,
        caption: 'All 1,568 heads projected onto the (V/Q, entropy) plane. Four non-overlapping clusters — architecture-invariant.',
      },
      {
        n: '3b', title: 'The Entropy-Collapse Scatterplot',
        src: `${base}/figures/fig3_scatter.png`,
        caption: 'Functional clustering of attention heads based on behaviour across structural and semantic stress tests.',
      },
      {
        n: '7', title: 'Lexical Anatomy',
        src: `${base}/figures/fig7_lexical.png`,
        caption: 'Top attended vocabulary items by head type on WikiText-103. Sink heads target punctuation; Induction heads show maximum focus.',
      },
      {
        n: '8', title: 'The Initialization Null',
        src: `${base}/figures/fig8_universality.png`,
        caption: 'Random-init GPT-2 (top) has no V/Q structure. Trained GPT-2 (bottom) develops the universal law. Structure is emergent from gradient descent.',
      },
      {
        n: '9', title: 'The Permutation Null',
        src: `${base}/figures/fig9_permutation.png`,
        caption: 'Induction heads fire equally on shuffled gibberish — proving they are structural pattern detectors, not language detectors.',
      },
      {
        n: '10', title: 'The Cross-Domain Proof',
        src: `${base}/figures/fig10_crossdomain.png`,
        caption: 'V/Q scaling law across WebText (GPT-2), multilingual (Qwen), and instruction (Llama). Same slope, different training universes.',
      },
      {
        n: '11', title: 'Projected Speedup Curves',
        src: `${base}/figures/fig11_speedup.png`,
        caption: 'FLOP-model projections from measured head fractions. Qwen-0.5B reaches 7.7× at N=32K; bounded by the critical-head ceiling.',
      },
      {
        n: '12', title: 'KV Cache Geometry',
        src: `${base}/figures/fig12_geometry.png`,
        caption: '3D PCA of Key vectors: Local heads form time-curves, Retrieval heads cluster semantically, untrained controls are amorphous clouds.',
      },
    ].map(f => (
      <div class="evidence-item reveal">
        <div class="evidence-meta">
          <span class="evidence-n">Figure {f.n}</span>
          <h3 class="evidence-title">{f.title}</h3>
          <p class="evidence-caption">{f.caption}</p>
        </div>
        <figure class="evidence-fig">
          <img src={f.src} alt={f.title} loading="lazy" />
        </figure>
      </div>
    ))}
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ── NAVIGATION ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="nav-doors">
  <div class="nav-doors-inner">
    <div class="door-grid reveal">
      {[
        { href: `${base}/taxonomy`,     no: '01', label: 'Taxonomy',         sub: 'V/Q law · bifurcation · atlas' },
        { href: `${base}/universality`, no: '02', label: 'Universality',     sub: 'Untrained null · permutation · cross-domain' },
        { href: `${base}/causal`,       no: '03', label: 'Causal Mechanics', sub: 'Co-gating · 96.5% · perplexity illusion' },
        { href: `${base}/systems`,      no: '04', label: 'Systems Impact',   sub: '13.3× KV compression · FLOP projections' },
        { href: `${base}/explorer`,     no: '05', label: 'Head Explorer',    sub: 'All 1,568 heads · interactive 3D', hl: true },
        { href: `${base}/report`,       no: '06', label: 'Full Report',      sub: 'Complete technical write-up' },
      ].map(d => (
        <a href={d.href} class={`door ${d.hl ? 'door-hl' : ''}`}>
          <span class="door-no">{d.no}</span>
          <span class="door-label">{d.label}</span>
          <span class="door-sub">{d.sub}</span>
        </a>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</Layout>

<script>
  const BASE = (document.querySelector('meta[name="base"]') as any)?.content
    ?? '/attentionheadgenome';

  fetch(`${BASE}/canonical_labels.json`)
    .then(r => r.json())
    .then(data => {
      const canvas = document.getElementById('atlas-canvas') as HTMLCanvasElement;
      if (!canvas) return;
      const ctx = canvas.getContext('2d')!;

      const isDark = () => document.documentElement.getAttribute('data-theme') === 'dark';
      const C: Record<string, () => string> = {
        sink:      () => isDark() ? '#ff6b6b' : '#c0392b',
        local:     () => isDark() ? '#5ac8fa' : '#2c5282',
        retrieval: () => isDark() ? '#bf5af2' : '#6b46c1',
        induction: () => isDark() ? '#ff9f0a' : '#c05621',
      };

      const models = Object.entries(data.models);
      const heads: any[] = [];
      models.forEach(([, mdata]: any, mi) => {
        const nL = mdata.n_layers;
        const allH = Object.values(mdata.heads) as any[];
        const maxH = Math.max(...allH.map((h: any) => h.head_idx));
        allH.forEach((hd: any) => {
          heads.push({
            label: hd.label,
            tx: (mi + (hd.head_idx + 0.5) / (maxH + 1)) / models.length,
            ty: (hd.layer + 0.5) / nL,
            x: Math.random(), y: Math.random(),
          });
        });
      });

      let frame = 0; const FRAMES = 90;
      const ease = (t: number) => t < 0.5 ? 2*t*t : -1+(4-2*t)*t;

      function resize() {
        const dpr = devicePixelRatio || 1;
        const r = canvas.getBoundingClientRect();
        canvas.width = r.width * dpr; canvas.height = r.height * dpr;
        ctx.scale(dpr, dpr);
      }
      resize();
      window.addEventListener('resize', () => { resize(); frame = 0; animate(); }, { passive: true });

      function draw() {
        const w = canvas.getBoundingClientRect().width;
        const h = canvas.getBoundingClientRect().height;
        ctx.clearRect(0, 0, w, h);
        const ep = ease(Math.min(frame / FRAMES, 1));
        heads.forEach(hd => {
          const x = (hd.x + (hd.tx - hd.x) * ep) * w;
          const y = (hd.y + (hd.ty - hd.y) * ep) * h;
          ctx.beginPath();
          ctx.arc(x, y, 3, 0, Math.PI * 2);
          ctx.fillStyle = C[hd.label]?.() ?? '#888';
          ctx.globalAlpha = 0.25 + 0.75 * ep;
          ctx.fill();
        });
        ctx.globalAlpha = 1;
      }

      let raf: number;
      function animate() {
        draw(); frame++;
        if (frame <= FRAMES + 5) raf = requestAnimationFrame(animate);
      }

      const obs = new IntersectionObserver(es => {
        if (es[0].isIntersecting) { frame = 0; animate(); obs.disconnect(); }
      });
      obs.observe(canvas);

      document.getElementById('theme-btn')?.addEventListener('click', () => {
        setTimeout(() => { frame = 0; animate(); }, 80);
      });
    })
    .catch(() => {});
</script>

<meta name="base" content="/attentionheadgenome" />

<style>
/* ── Hero ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.hero {
  min-height: 100vh;
  display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
  padding: 8rem 2.5rem 5rem;
  text-align: center;
  background: radial-gradient(ellipse 100% 50% at 50% -5%, rgba(0,113,227,.08) 0%, transparent 65%);
}
[data-theme="light"] .hero {
  background: radial-gradient(ellipse 100% 50% at 50% -5%, rgba(0,113,227,.04) 0%, transparent 65%);
}
.hero-inner { max-width: 720px; }
.hero-eyebrow {
  font-size: .72rem; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: .14em;
  text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--text-3);
  margin-bottom: 2.5rem; display: block;
}
.hero-title {
  font-size: clamp(3rem, 9vw, 7rem);
  font-weight: 200; letter-spacing: -.05em; line-height: 1.0;
  margin-bottom: 1.75rem; font-family: var(--font);
}
.hero-sub {
  font-size: 1.2rem; color: var(--text-2); font-weight: 300;
  line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 3.5rem;
}

/* README-style numbered findings */
.findings-list {
  list-style: none; counter-reset: findings;
  text-align: left; margin: 0 0 3rem;
  display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.25rem;
}
.findings-list li {
  counter-increment: findings;
  display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1.6rem 1fr;
  gap: 0 1rem; font-size: .9rem; line-height: 1.55;
  align-items: baseline;
}
.findings-list li::before {
  content: counter(findings);
  font-size: .72rem; font-weight: 500; color: var(--accent);
  font-family: var(--mono); padding-top: .15rem;
}
.findings-list strong {
  display: block; font-weight: 500; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: .2rem;
  font-size: .9rem;
}
.findings-list span { color: var(--text-2); font-weight: 300; }
.findings-list li > span { /* wraps strong + text */ grid-column: 2; }
/* re-structure so strong and span stack */
.findings-list li { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1.6rem 1fr; gap: 0 1rem; }
.findings-list li strong { grid-column: 2; }
.findings-list li > :not(strong):not(::before) { grid-column: 2; }

.hero-actions { display: flex; gap: 1rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
.hero-btn-primary {
  background: var(--accent); color: white;
  padding: .75rem 2rem; border-radius: 2rem;
  text-decoration: none; font-size: .95rem; font-weight: 400;
  transition: opacity .2s, transform .2s;
}
.hero-btn-primary:hover { opacity: .85; transform: translateY(-1px); }
.hero-btn-secondary {
  border: 1px solid var(--border-med); color: var(--text);
  padding: .75rem 2rem; border-radius: 2rem;
  text-decoration: none; font-size: .95rem; font-weight: 300;
  transition: background .2s;
}
.hero-btn-secondary:hover { background: var(--bg2); }

/* ── Numbers ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.numbers-section { max-width: 960px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 2rem 8rem; }

/* ── Atlas section ───────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.atlas-section { background: var(--bg2); padding: 8rem 2.5rem; }
.atlas-inner {
  max-width: 1000px; margin: 0 auto;
  display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.2fr; gap: 5rem; align-items: center;
}
@media (max-width: 760px) { .atlas-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 3rem; } }
.atlas-text h2 {
  font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3vw, 2.4rem);
  font-weight: 200; letter-spacing: -.04em; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; line-height: 1.15;
}
.atlas-text p { color: var(--text-2); font-weight: 300; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
.type-pills { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: .5rem; }
#atlas-canvas {
  width: 100%; height: 320px; display: block;
  border-radius: var(--radius); background: var(--bg);
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
}
.atlas-caption { font-size: .75rem; color: var(--text-3); margin-top: .75rem; text-align: center; }

/* ── Nav doors ───────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.nav-doors { padding: 8rem 2.5rem; }
.nav-doors-inner { max-width: 960px; margin: 0 auto; }
.door-grid {
  display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr));
  gap: 1px; background: var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius);
  overflow: hidden; margin-top: 0;
}
.door {
  background: var(--bg); padding: 2rem 2rem 1.75rem;
  text-decoration: none; color: var(--text);
  display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: .35rem;
  transition: background .2s;
}
[data-theme="dark"] .door { background: var(--bg2); }
.door:hover { background: var(--surface); backdrop-filter: var(--glass-blur); }
.door-hl { background: var(--bg2) !important; }
[data-theme="dark"] .door-hl { background: #0d0d0d !important; }
.door-no { font-size: .65rem; font-family: var(--mono); color: var(--accent); font-weight: 500; }
.door-label { font-size: 1.05rem; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: -.02em; }
.door-sub { font-size: .78rem; color: var(--text-3); font-weight: 300; line-height: 1.4; }

/* ── Evidence / figures story ────────────────────────────────── */
.evidence-section { padding: 8rem 2.5rem; }
.evidence-inner { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; }
.evidence-intro {
  color: var(--text-2); font-weight: 300; font-size: 1rem;
  margin-bottom: 5rem; max-width: 560px;
}
.evidence-item {
  display: grid; grid-template-columns: 220px 1fr; gap: 4rem;
  align-items: start; padding: 5rem 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
}
.evidence-item:last-child { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
@media (max-width: 760px) {
  .evidence-item { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 1.5rem; }
}
.evidence-meta { position: sticky; top: 6rem; }
.evidence-n {
  font-size: .65rem; font-family: var(--mono); font-weight: 500;
  color: var(--text-3); letter-spacing: .08em; display: block; margin-bottom: .5rem;
}
.evidence-title {
  font-size: 1.15rem; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: -.025em;
  margin-bottom: .75rem; line-height: 1.3;
}
.evidence-caption {
  font-size: .82rem; color: var(--text-3); font-weight: 300; line-height: 1.6;
}
.evidence-fig { margin: 0; }
.evidence-fig img {
  width: 100%; border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
}
</style>
